title: Wilson volleyball rallies to down Luray
text:
Wilson volleyball rallies to down Luray Staff Report 9:17 p.m. EDT October 13, 2015 File photo CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
FISHERSVILLE â€” Abby Taylor powered down 14 kills and Hannah Johnson 13 to lead Wilson Memorial past Luray 19-25, 25-11, 28-26, 25-22 in volleyball action on Tuesday. 
Johnson added 11 assists and 23 digs while Emma Harrison contributed 15 assists, two blocks and six aces. 
"The team played really well," Wilson coach Lauren Grove said. "We did a great job of fighting when we were down. It was a great team effort overall." 
Wilson's jayvees won in three sets. Read or Share this story: http://www.newsleader.com/story/sports/2015/10/13/wilson-volleyball-rallies-down-luray/73901296/ TOP VIDEOS
